### Description

**Description**
When using a Waystone from the Waystones mod to teleport from a fixed static location in the world to a player-built simulated physics contraption (sub-level structure from Sable/Create Simulated) in a single-player world, the client will encounter either of the following two issues:
_1. Severe client freeze: The game completely locks up for approximately 10-15 seconds, with no input response, before eventually recovering.
2.Chunk loading failure & crash:
 1)Immediately after teleport, the render distance drops to 1 chunk
 2)All blocks lose collision, allowing the player to clip through the world/terrain
After ~10-15 seconds, the client throws a network protocol error, displays a "connection lost" message, and crashes back to the main menu._
**Reproduction Steps**
_1.Create a single-player world with Sable, Create Simulated and Waystones installed
2.Build a valid physics contraption (simulated sub-level structure), then place a Waystone on the contraption
3.Place another Waystone at a fixed, static location in the world (not on any simulated contraption)
4.Use the fixed static Waystone to teleport directly to the Waystone placed on the physics contraption_
**Environment**
Minecraft Version: 1.21.1
Mod Loader: NeoForge 21.1.226
Sable Version: 1.0.6
Create Simulated Version: 1.0.3
Waystones Version: waystones-neoforge-1.21.1-21.1.29
Game Type: Single-player world

### Game Log

none

